.TH "efi_mem_reserve" 9 "efi_mem_reserve" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
efi_mem_reserve \- Reserve an EFI memory region
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" efi_mem_reserve
.BI "(phys_addr_t addr "  ","
.BI "u64 size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "addr" 12
Physical address to reserve
.IP "size" 12
Size of reservation
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Mark a region as reserved from general kernel allocation and
prevent it being released by \fBefi_free_boot_services\fP.

This function should be called drivers once they've parsed EFI
configuration tables to figure out where their data lives, e.g.
\fBefi_esrt_init\fP.
